    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Valves</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove carbon deposits from valve stems and valve heads.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect each valve, replacing any that show excessive burn marks, warping, scuffing,
                bending, or valve tip spalling.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3900011" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8590.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Valve stem measurement points</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Two measurements 90 degrees apart</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Three valve stem diameter measurement locations</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure each valve stem diameter for wear using a 0-1 inch micrometer. Measure valves at
                three locations 90&#176; apart and record readings. Replace valves not within minimum stem diameter
                <hotlnk document="eges390_291.xml" xrefid="E30005A">specification
                    <xref refid="E30005A"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The intake valve has a larger diameter head.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the valve guide inside diameters measured earlier and the valve stem diameter
                measurements just recorded, determine valve stem-to-guide running clearance. Replace valve or cylinder
                head as required. See
                <hotlnk document="eges390_291.xml" xrefid="E30005A">Specifications
                    <xref refid="E30005A"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e300554" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0874.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Measuring the valve face</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure the valve face margin at four locations (90&#176; apart) using a dial caliper.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, the minimum valve face margin must be maintained across the entire valve
                    face. An insufficient margin will not provide proper heat dissipation and lead to valve warping or
                    breakage. Intake and exhaust valve margins are different. Replace valve if the margin is less than
                    the specified minimum. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_291.xml" xrefid="E30005A">Specifications
                        <xref refid="E30005A"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </caution>
            <note>
                <para>If valves and seats are in a serviceable condition, they may be re-faced to the specified angles.
                    See
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_291.xml" xrefid="E30005A">Specifications
                        <xref refid="E30005A"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcsubproc>
